==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Permeable
<hw>Per"me*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>permeabilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>perm⟦eacute⟧able</ets>. See
<er>Permeate</er>.]</ety> <def>Capable of being permeated, or passed
through; yielding passage; passable; penetrable; -- used especially of
substances which allow the passage of fluids; <as>as, wood is
<ex>permeable</ex> to oil; glass is <ex>permeable</ex> to
light.</as></def> <rj><au>I. Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Permeably</ent>⟦br⟧
